s and injustices. By showing how sharing a dancefloor involves feeling, touch, sound, sexuality, and subculture, Garcia-Mispireta rethinks intimacy and belonging through dancing crowds and the utopian vision of throbbing dancefloors.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAffect (Psychology). 0aDancexSocial aspects. 0aElectronic dance musicxSocial aspectszFrancezParis. 0aElectronic dance musicxSocial aspectszGermanyzBerlin. 0aElectronic dance musicxSocial aspectszIllinoiszChicago. 0aElectronic dance musicxSocial aspects. 0aEthnomusicology. 0aHouse musicxSocial aspects. 0aIntimacy (Psychology). 0aMusic and dancexSocial aspects. 0aNightlife. 0aSound effects music. 7aMUSIC / Ethnomusicology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478027058?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478027058423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478027058/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles